<p>Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy will publish a prison memoir, “Diary of a Prisoner,” on December 10 via publisher Fayard [lemonde.fr#1][abcnews.go.com#1]. The book recounts 20 days he spent in Paris’s La Santé prison this autumn [politico.eu#1][lemonde.fr#1]. The release comes as he appeals a conviction tied to efforts to obtain 2007 campaign funds from Libya; an appeals court approved his release on November 10 [politico.eu#1][theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/GfvNcysz5dySdLujOD79NJ0Rcj16A9cBFUOhPn7_CI1WlLNdpLi0wmfhFqVFhKbQbjUUXoSfbRRxSJfC19oHHnIFTST155ax4VxYqu8i26QBL2Oryw8e9m6I0nMIYngAaIwatReOdozVyhdwyQ_PkUgVrR5f4siApZqRcQ-vEw' alt='Former French President Nicolas Sarkozy, whose prison memoir is due December 10' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Publication details: Release set for Dec. 10 via Fayard; the book is 216 pages long [lemonde.fr#1][abcnews.go.com#1][politico.eu#1]</li><li>Time in custody: Covers 20 days in La Santé prison in Paris during autumn 2025 [politico.eu#1][theguardian.com#1][lemonde.fr#1]</li><li>Detention conditions: He was separated from the general prison population; two bodyguards occupied a neighboring cell for safety [politico.eu#1]</li><li>Legal backdrop: He is appealing a conviction related to attempts to obtain financing from Moammar Gadhafi’s regime for his 2007 campaign; an appeals court approved his release on Nov. 10 [theguardian.com#1][politico.eu#1]</li><li>Teaser excerpt: “In prison, there is nothing to see, and nothing to do.” He also writes that noise at La Santé “is alas constant.” [politico.eu#1]</li></ul><blockquote>In prison, there is nothing to see, and nothing to do. - Nicolas Sarkozy</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Nicolas Sarkozy: He frames the experience as an inner journey, writing that “like [in] the desert, inner life strengthens in prison.” [politico.eu#1] (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nothing-to-see-and-nothing-to-do-nicolas-sarkozy-release-prison-memoir/'>POLITICO Europe</a>)</li><li>Fayard (publisher): Announced the Dec. 10 release of “Diary of a Prisoner.” [abcnews.go.com#1] (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/french-president-sarkozy-publish-prison-memoir-appeal-looms-127749985'>ABC News</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/21/nicolas-sarkozy-to-publish-book-about-his-20-days-in-prison'>Nicolas Sarkozy to write prison memoir on his 20 days in jail</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nothing-to-see-and-nothing-to-do-nicolas-sarkozy-release-prison-memoir/'>Sarkozy pens 216-page prison memoir recounting mini-break behind bars</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2025/11/21/sarkozy-to-publish-new-memoir-diary-of-a-prisoner-ahead-of-appeal_6747703_7.html'>Sarkozy to publish new memoir, &#x27;Diary of a Prisoner,&#x27; ahead of appeal</a> - lemonde.fr</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/french-president-sarkozy-publish-prison-memoir-appeal-looms-127749985'>Ex-French President Sarkozy to publish prison memoir as appeal looms</a> - abcnews.go.com</li></ul>